@startuml
' @id(USE-MAP-MOCKUPS)
' @desc(USE-MAP-MOCKUPS, "When /mdd-map runs at whole-repository scope it auto-includes mockup diagrams: for any UI app it finds in the repo (today the repo-root mockups/ React app) it authors a current-side Salt mockup under .mdd/models/current/mockups/<name>.puml carrying an MCK- id whose @ui-element UIC ids mirror the app's data-testids, so the current map is complete across all diagram kinds rather than the five UML kinds only. At feature/module scope mockups stay opt-in (produced only when asked or warranted), matching how sequences/domain/components behave. Realized by SEQ-MAP-MOCKUPS; owned by CMP-MAP-SKILL.")
title MDD map — auto-include mockups for whole-repo scope (objective)

left to right direction

actor "Developer / Agent" as Dev

rectangle "/mdd-map skill" {
  usecase "Map the whole repository\n(all diagram kinds)" as MapWhole
  usecase "Auto-include mockups\nfor any UI app found" as MapMockups
}

Dev --> MapWhole
MapWhole ..> MapMockups : <<include>>

note bottom of MapMockups
  Objective (USE-MAP-MOCKUPS): whole-repo scope emits current-side
  MCK- Salt mockups for discovered UI apps (e.g. mockups/), with
  UIC ids mirroring data-testids. Feature/module scope keeps
  mockups opt-in.
end note
@enduml
